President Donald Trump awarded the Presidential Medal of Freedom to former Congressman Jim Ryun, a legendary athlete and runner. In his remarks, President Trump highlighted Ryun's athletic achievements, including breaking the four-minute mile barrier in high school and setting multiple world records in the mile and half mile events. Ryun's dedication to his sport and his humility were praised, and his impact as a mentor and his commitment to his Christian faith were also noted. Ryun thanked the President and expressed his gratitude for the honor, attributing his success to God and his family.